    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between Milwaukee M18 and M12?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>M18</strong> is Milwaukee's 18-volt platform \u2014 the primary system for heavy-duty trade applications with over 275 cordless solutions including drills, saws, grinders and rotary hammers. <strong>M12</strong> is the compact 12-volt platform designed for tight-space work and lighter-duty applications like inspection cameras, sub-compact drills and pipe cutters. Both systems use REDLITHIUM batteries, but they are not cross-compatible \u2014 M18 batteries only fit M18 tools and M12 batteries only fit M12 tools.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does FUEL mean on Milwaukee tools?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>M18 FUEL</strong> is Milwaukee's top-tier professional range within the M18 platform. FUEL tools feature three exclusive technologies: the <strong>POWERSTATE brushless motor</strong> for maximum power and durability, <strong>REDLITHIUM battery packs</strong> for extended runtime, and <strong>REDLINK PLUS intelligence</strong> for real-time communication between tool and battery. FUEL tools deliver up to 20% more power and 40% faster cutting speed than non-FUEL equivalents.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Milwaukee ONE-KEY and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>ONE-KEY</strong> is Milwaukee's digital platform for tools and equipment. It allows you to <strong>track tool locations</strong> via Bluetooth, <strong>customise tool settings</strong> such as speed and torque for specific applications, and <strong>manage your entire inventory</strong> across multiple jobsites from one app. ONE-KEY is built into compatible M18 FUEL tools and can also be added to non-ONE-KEY tools via a ONE-KEY TICK tracker.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the PACKOUT system and is it worth it?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>PACKOUT</strong> is Milwaukee's modular storage system \u2014 the most versatile on the market. Every PACKOUT box, organiser, tote and rolling chest <strong>interlocks securely</strong> so you can stack and transport your entire kit as one unit. Boxes are <strong>IP65 weather-sealed</strong> and built with impact-resistant polymer. For tradespeople moving between sites daily, PACKOUT eliminates loose tool bags and disorganised vans. It is the industry standard for professional tool storage.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Milwaukee tools come with in the UK?",
            "answer": "<p>Milwaukee power tools come with a standard manufacturer warranty. By <strong>registering your tool within 30 days of purchase</strong> on the Milwaukee warranty portal, you can extend this to a <strong>3-year warranty</strong>. As an official UK stockist, Invicta Tools can assist with all warranty claims and support. Register at <strong>warranty.milwaukeetool.eu</strong> with your proof of purchase.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Milwaukee tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Milwaukee range including M18 FUEL, M12, PACKOUT and accessories. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
